<item>
            <title>[OGNL-6] When setting fields type conversion returning null falsly reports a NoSuchPropertyException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OGNL-6</link>
                <project id="12313525" key="OGNL">Commons OGNL (Dormant)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When calling a method, if type conversion fails (returns null), a parameter is just set to null and then the method is called.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When setting a field, if type conversion (returns null), the field set is skipped altogether and a NoSuchPropertyException is thrown. Instead, the field should be set to null to be parallel with method calling and not report a false exception.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
