                            <comment id="13395504" author="jkuhnert" created="Sat, 17 Feb 2007 12:37:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Need more time to confirm this behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13395546" author="jkuhnert" created="Sat, 14 Apr 2007 13:42:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed this recently so that if type conversion fails a catchable exception is thrown.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13395723" author="erikjogi" created="Thu, 21 May 2009 06:41:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just stumbled on this issue when using OGNL in Struts2. I have a custom TypeConverter that returns null sometimes. This returned value is ignored and a NoSuchPropertyException is thrown. &lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;I agree with the original description that possibility to set null values to a field shoud be supported. &lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Can you please comment as to why won&apos;t you fix this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
